Andrey Ulanov writes:
 > Look at this:
 > 
 > $ cat test.c
 > #include <stdio.h>
 > 
 > main()
 > {
 > 	double h = 0.2;
 > 
 > 	if(1/h == 5.0)
 > 	    printf("1/h == 5.0\n");
 > 
 > 	if(1/h < 5.0)
 > 	    printf("1/h < 5.0\n");
 > 	return 0;
 > }
 > $ gcc test.c
$ gcc -O test.c
$ ./a.out
1/h == 5.0
without -O, gcc initializes h to 0.2000000000000000111
 > $ ./a.out
 > 1/h < 5.0
 > $ 
